CORE GAMEPLY
The game is mostly based on the ever popular game Bloons Tower Defense created by Ninja Kiwi
The game reects some of the concepts presented by its predecessor in which it has:
Place able towers which have dierent strengths and abilies.
A system in which you may create your own map and paths for the balloons to travel on.
o There are some know issues that may aect the gameplay experience (listed later in
this document).
A loading screen (Its just there for help with future development, more on this later)
Ability to create custom towers (for now it is only possible through eding the source).
Dierent balloon types with dierent heath and speeds.
POTENTIAL EXCEPTIONS AND PROBLEMS
Though my expectaons were merely reached through some of the implementaon of concepts
that produced high end game design (i.e. mul-threading though I could not nd a place to use
this at, more on this later).
Some computers may not be able to handle the calculaons required in this game if there is a
medium amount of load on the system, caused by background tasks like Chrome and
Photoshop.
Somemes the towers will glitch and not shoot the balloons

BALLOON.JAVA
DESCRIPTION:
This class is the super object of all other balloon classes (BalloonRed etc).
It controls most of the tasks needed to perform for the balloon to render on to the screen and is
the heart of the balloon framework. Like movement and health, hits and drawing and most
importantly rewarding the player money if the balloon is in fact popped.

METHODS:
Balloon(int, int, FloorGrid, BalloonType)
Descripon:
constructor a balloon object is created with the following as parameters int
oorX, int oorY, FloorGrid grid, BalloonType type
the balloon is spawned on the oorX and oorY coordinates and the default
values provided by the type specied
Balloon(Texture, Floor, FloorGrid, int, int, oat, oat)
Descripon:
constructor a balloon object is created with the following as parameters
Texture instanceTexture, Floor starngFloorObject, FloorGrid grid, int
width, int height, oat speed, oat health
the balloon is created with a texture and spawned on the starngFloorObject
with a width and height and speed and health
ck()
Descripon:
ck is called every loop of the main game loop to update the current factors
of the balloons posion and checks if the balloon is alive and gets the next
turning point and moves the balloon depending on the speed and the direcons
array
isTurningPointReached()
Descripon:
returns true if the turning point has been reached
endReached()
Descripon:
This pops the balloon if it makes it through the enre way without beeing
poped and subtracts a life from the player

Balloons Tower Defense

damage(int)
Descripon:
damages the balloon object and requires a damage parameter to subtract from
the health if the health is 0 or less then added the specied amount of
money to the player object
ndDirecon(Floor)
Descripon:
ndDirecon returns a int array which contains two values represent if the
balloon should move in either axis
post: returns a direcon array that contains values either 1, 2, 0, -1
represenng movement if the value is 1 then the balloon moves by
mullplieing the speed and delta by 1 otherwise it returns 2 if the end is
reached and 0 if the movement is not required in either the x or y axis also
it is -1 one if it is going backwards or against the axis in this case if it
is -1 on the 1st index then it is going up on the y axis
llTurningPointArrayList()
Descripon:
Fills the array list of turning point objects containing all direconal
object for maneuvering the balloon object it loops through ul it nds the
end of the path using a basic guess and check algorithm path nding
algorithm,
post: the turning point list is lled with all the turning points discovered
in the map
ndTurningPoint(Floor, int[])
Descripon:
Returns an object represenng the current turning point by looping through
all possibilites of the checkpoint's locaon up, down, le, right from the
current locaon starng oor is the object currently on.
In summary this algorithm is more complicated to explain then to make it
